1000147.text: Shards of the Mirror of Irminsul are scattered <color=#82C65D>within the tower</color>. It seems that something strange will happen when they are all collected.

1000148.text: You have collected all the shards. $B$Go to the <color=#82C65D>Hall of Irminsul</color> to unravel the puzzle.

1000150.text: Explore the Irminsul Woods and find out how the giant tree appeared.

1000152.text: Proceed and investigate the cause of the mutations of the forest biology.

1000155.text: Phrygia the Frog Chevalier has lost his beloved <color=#82C65D>Pot</color>. Keep an eye out for it during your explorations.

1000156.text: Phrygia's <color=#82C65D>wand</color> is also missing; how careless of him! Help him find it during your journey.

1000159.text: You have found the lost wand. Return it to Phrygia. He should be at the <color=#82C65D>Giant Tree Periphery</color>.

1000161.text: Deluca noticed that a mysterious girl had entered the upper level of the Chrono Tower. Continue exploring up the Tower.

1000162.text: Snegurochka witnessed the end of the War of Protectors. Perhaps you will find your answer there.

1000163.text: You have reached Snegurochka Mountain. Take some time to look around.

1000164.text: It is said the blizzard was brought about by the magic circle at the peak. Climb to the <color=#82C65D>peak</color>, and you may find a way to stop the blizzard.

1000165.text: Defeat Saintess Cersivey at <color=#82C65D>Saintess Square</color> at the peak, and calm the blizzard.

1000166.text: Help the wounded hunter and deliver the message to <color=#82C65D>Silverbow</color>.

1000167.text: Find Silverbow at <color=#82C65D>Frozen Lake Hunting Grounds: Middle</color>, and try to reconcile Silverbow and the Old Hunter.

1000168.text: There seems to be some kind of misunderstanding between the wolves and humans. Persuading the Leader of the Pack may improve their relations.

1000169.text: Anemone lost her Flame Emblem while escaping. Find <color=#82C65D>Anemone</color> and return the Flame Emblem to her.

1000170.text: Go on up and explore the secrets of the Chrono Tower.

1000171.text: Dejase is distracting the monsters single-handedly. Bluen is worried about her. <color=#82C65D>Explore upwards</color>, and confirm that Dejase is safe.

1000172.text: Use Intangible Shifting again, and try to prevent the destruction of Snegurochka.

1000173.text: After Intangible Shifting, Snegurochka seems different than before. Have a look around.

1000174.text: Go on exploring, and find out the reason why Cersivey created the blizzard.

1000175.text: Cersivey set up a powerful Boundary. Search for clues outside the Boundary.

1000176.text: The place where magic can be felt the strongest is the Foothills Hunting Grounds. Maybe you can find the entrance there.

1000177.text: You have entered the boundary forged by Cersivey. Search the inside for anything unusual.

1000178.text: There are suspicious creatures inside the Boundary. Proceed with caution.

1000179.text: Cersivey has created the blizzard in the hope of offsetting the Geothermy, but she refuses any help. <color=#82C65D>Continue exploring</color> and investigate the source of the Geothermy.

1000180.text: These suspicious creatures may have something to do with the Geothermy. Search <color=#82C65D>Saintess Square</color> and find where the creatures are appearing from.

1000181.text: Catch up with Cersivey and find out what the source of the Geothermy is.

1000182.text: Sinmara's lava core is the key to saving Snegurochka from devastation. Inquire the <color=#82C65D>Captain of the Frost Chivalric Order</color> about clues to the Frost of Absolute Zero.

1000183.text: You have received the Ice Cryolite from the Captain and the Eternal Ice from Cersivey. Next, you need to find La Crima who is believed to be at the <color=#82C65D>Castle: Front</color>.

1000184.text: Defeat Sinmara, and reverse the fate of Snegurochka's doom.

1000185.text: Go on up and explore the secrets of the Chrono Tower.

1000186.text: Entrusted by the elder brother who has become a caterpillar, you need to venture into the <color=#82C65D>Forest ahead</color> and find his strayed little brother.

1000187.text: Soleil wants to retrieve his precious songbook. Search for it at the <color=#82C65D>Northern Commercial Area</color>, and go back to him at the <color=#82C65D>Sentry Camp</color>.

1000188.text: The merchant's favorite armor is at this shop in the market at the <color=#82C65D>Commercial Area Entry</color>. Retrieve his armor.

1000189.text: After getting his songbook, Soleil seems to be acting a little strange. Go quickly and see what is going on.

1000190.text: The merchant hid his gold and silver under the floor of his shop in the <color=#82C65D>Commercial Area</color>. Retrieve his hidden gold and silver.

1000191.text: All the merchant has left is some savings buried in his hometown. Explore Irene Island, and help him back home.

1000192.text: The most precious thing is the homeland in one's heart. Fulfill the merchant's last wish by finding his real home on <color=#82C65D>Irene Island</color>.

1000193.text: Deliver the news to the anxious elder brother that his younger brother has also turned into a caterpillar. He is at either the <color=#82C65D>Commercial Area</color> or the <color=#82C65D>Giant Tree: Periphery</color>.

1000194.text: Help villager Andy find the <color=#82C65D>proper wood for making a crutch</color>. He will swap treasure with you for it.

1000195.text: Villager's crops were stolen by cunning foxes. Find the stolen crops, and teach the foxes a lesson.

1000196.text: A snow wolf stole Silverbow's luggage. Return the luggage to him. It is said he is at <color=#82C65D>Pass of Talus: End</color>.

1000197.text: Escort the wounded wolf cub back home.

1000198.text: The White Bear often attacks humans nearby. Collect info about the White Bear's whereabouts. <color=#82C65D>Silverbow</color> might know something; keep an eye out for him on your journey.

1000199.text: Slay the savage <color=#82C65D>White Bear</color> so that it will no longer harm humans.

1000200.text: The young man's bow was taken away during the hunting altercation. Retrieve his bow. He is waiting on the <color=#82C65D>Frozen Lake Surface</color> ahead.

1000201.text: Find the Leader of the Pack on the <color=#82C65D>Foothills Tundra</color>.

1000202.text: The Little Fox must be hoarding the food <color=#82C65D>nearby</color>. Have a look around.

1001047.text: To carry out the Deliverer's duty, as well as save his friend, Kyphon decides to chase <color=#82C65D>Goorveig</color> alone.

1001048.text: Help Kyphon find the fleeing Goorveig.

1001049.text: Goorveig is in danger. Find her ASAP.

1001050.text: Find a way to get Dejase back to normal.

1001051.text: The Preacher has gone to another world with the forbidden magic. Find out what he's been plotting.

1001052.text: Escort the mysterious girl Lyne to her companions.

1001053.text: Go north and harvest the <color=#82C65D>White Flower</color> that stops bleeding.

1001054.text: You have collected the White Flower. Deliver it to Tuonel in the village who is waiting anxiously.

1001055.text: Light a pile of leaves on fire under the tree at the <color=#82C65D>Entrance to the Flower Fields</color>. It's the code signal to contact the leader of the Alliance of the Rebellions. Tell him what happened.

1001056.text: The villager hid the crops in a secret path in the flower fields. Confirm her crops are safe.

1001057.text: Someone saw a suspicious preacher near the Lower Domain stage. Investigate that area for clues.

1001058.text: The preacher was spotted in the Ruins of Pelenier Village. Investigate that area for clues.

1001059.text: There's some strange <color=#82C65D>rumors</color> going around about the earthquakes that are worth investigating.

1001060.text: It seems the Preacher is manipulating monsters to attack the innocent. You have to stop him.

1001061.text: The naughty Afallen strayed into the Lower Domain. It's unsafe to tread alone. Escort her back to the <color=#82C65D>Upper Domain</color>.

1001062.text: Garditis is contacting his comrades nearby. Inform him to be careful for that he is targeted by assassins.

1001063.text: Team up to defeat the giant monster perching in the Lower Domain.

1001064.text: Give <color=#82C65D>Nemesi</color> the salve made by Tuonel.

1001065.text: The earthquakes are not a simple matter of monsters. Enter the Upper Domain to find the truth.
